This move does not look especially bad at first glance but remembering some of the team tips here are a few pointers 
- usually develop N and B before R or Q 
- early Q development can leave it vulnerable 
- Q is blocking f6 (stops Nf6) 
- creates weaknesses like c7  
- Bc8 is still blocked in 
- still 2 moves required to castle
